description: SolTech Energy Sweden AB engages in the development and trade of solar energy products for commercial, public, and residential consumers. The company is headquartered in Stockholm, Stockholm and currently employs 196 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2015-06-25. The firm develops and sells building-integrated solar energy products for such forms of building structures as commercial, public and residential. The products are a part of a building’s outer shell, as a roof, wall or window, containing semi-transparent solar cells for the production of electricity that simultaneously shade out solar heat. The Company’s primary markets are the Nordic countries and China.
naics: Semiconductor and Other Electronic Component Manufacturing
